<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-018-169 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 585 100</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Nov 1991 v30 n14 p132(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tool assesses manufacturing concerns during PCB design.andO;(Manufacturing Advisor/PCB from Mentor Graphics)(printed circuitboard) (Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Donlin, Mike.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mentor Graphics introduces Manufacturing Advisor/PCB, priced at$16,900 and currently available for the HP/Apollo platform.andP;  Thesoftware is scheduled for a 1st qtr 1992 release for the Sun andHP Series 700 platforms.andP;  Manufacturing Advisor/PCB supportsconcurrent engineering and provides early identification ofparts-related manufacturing problems in PCB assemblies.andP;  Theeffects of recommended design alternatives can be tested withwhat-if analyses.andP;  Engineers can use Advisor/PCB prior toschematic capture, by entering a parts list and performingpreliminary analysis.andP;  The tool can identify parts that haveunique labor requirements, and the auto-insertability of eachcomponent selected for a particular design.andP;  A component libraryis available that has manufacturability information on over 800component package styles.andP;  Optional parts library is priced at$1,500.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mentor Graphics Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MENT.andO;Product:   Manufacturing Advisor/PCB (Performance analysis software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionDiagnostic AssessmentPerformance Analysis SoftwareCircuit DesignComponent ReliabilitySoftware Packages.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>